narrations.value: Since the buyer's journey doesn't stop when a prospect becomes a customer - as "expansion" is a key part of the buying experience -
I also influence upsells, cross-sells, license or seat increases, and add-ons to help expand revenue.

I can also conduct Customer or Partner Satisfaction, <sub alias="Net Promoter Score">NPS</sub>, <sub alias="Customer Effort Score">CES</sub> polls, and can automatically request promoters for new customer referrals in real-time.
Polls are 4 times more effective than surveys to gauge executive sentiment and feedback.
Again, speeding up onboarding accelerates value realization, leading to increased NRR.
Further, customer journeys begin before a prospect becomes a customer.
I can preboard late-stage prospects and set expectations and introduce teams, processes, and timeline.
I can onboard accounts, users, power users, executives, and non-line-of-business decision-makers<cast:nospeechfootnote>CFOs and CAOs</cast:nospeechfootnote> at the start of the customer journey.
Personalize learning experiences for new and existing users by persona.
Onboard add-on features, new products purchased,
and new user hires at any point in the customer lifecycle.
I can also re-onboard users when they start using a feature or product as a result of an adoption drive.
Finally, if you offer off-boarding experiences, to give leaving customers a reason to return, I should be able to help as well.
Conventionally, Frontline CSMs execute playbooks, present to, and advise your customers.
And occasionally bring in team members when needed.
With Cast.app, AI-driven Digital-CSMs (that would be me!) generate personalized presentations and present them to your customers on your behalf.
I digitize and execute playbooks, explaining and tying customer insights to recommendations that influence your customers to take actions that grow and preserve your revenue.
As a Digital AI <sub alias="Customer Success or Account Manager">CS/AM</sub>, I can bring in CSMs when needed, elevating CSMs to focus on new challenges and customer relationships.
I can also bring in Account Managers for sales and Subject Matter Experts for their expertise.
Let's take a look at the revenue metrics for Good Eats in the past month.
<cast:mark>Saturday, November 5, 2022</cast:mark> at <cast:mark>$22,000</cast:mark> was the highest revenue day and up by 16%.
Sundays continue to be your best selling days, totaling <cast:mark>$15,335</cast:mark> for the month of November.
Make sure you are adequately staffed during this day to handle your customer traffic.
If you have new items to feature, <cast:mark>Sunday</cast:mark> would be the best day to promote them.
According to our analysis, <cast:mark>6 PM</cast:mark> to <cast:mark>8 PM</cast:mark> is when you generated the most sales, an average of <cast:mark>$180</cast:mark> per customer.
The <cast:mark>New York Strip steak dinner</cast:mark> promotion in November was a huge success!  You should consider running similar promotions during these hours in the future.
Now let's look at Support Metrics using a data-driven widgets slide.
Average Resolution Time was under 40 minutes, well below the SLA for Acme Corporation, at 60 minutes during business days.
I can explain support tickets opened by day using a calendar heatmap!
Or by day of the week!
I can, for instance, execute a playbook if the number of open tickets does not drop after onboarding.
I can share predictions, e.g., if support professionals solve <cast:mark>600</cast:mark> tickets manually, you can solve <cast:mark>3700</cast:mark>, or 6x tickets by pairing automation and agents.
